main event: An unidentified object was sighted over Austin, Texas on November 8, 1966 at 5:47 PM.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a large, round, white object with one white light.
The object hovered in the sky at an elevation of 50-60 degrees.
The sighting lasted for 5-10 minutes and was observed by about 5-6 people.
The object did not move or change direction during the sighting.
The weather conditions were clear with no obstructions to visibility.
